LIMPOPO – Twelve people have been left injured after the state vehicle they were travelling in overturned along the N1 North near the Solomondale turnoff at around 10:00 on Sunday, 7 January 2018. Spokesman Matome Moremi, says the Iveco minibus was transporting newly recruited student officers to a local college when it overturned allegedly due to a burst tyre. “One passenger sustained critical injuries and eleven other including the driver sustained minor injuries. All injured were taken to a Polokwane hospital for treatment,” concludes Moremi. Read original story on capricornreview.co.za